# 301 redirects: old WordPress URLs -> new static pages
# Preserves SEO/link equity after the rebuild cutover.
# Format: <old path>  <new path>  <status>

# --- Canonical-host enforcement: kill duplicate-content from the
#     default Netlify subdomain. Any hit on the .netlify.app host is
#     force-301'd to the same path on the custom domain so Google
#     consolidates everything onto www.phonepsychicreaders.com and
#     drops the netlify.app version from its index over the next few
#     crawl cycles. The trailing "!" force flag means the redirect
#     happens even when the destination file exists. ---
https://superlative-tarsier-f12d9b.netlify.app/*  https://www.phonepsychicreaders.com/:splat  301!
http://superlative-tarsier-f12d9b.netlify.app/*   https://www.phonepsychicreaders.com/:splat  301!

# Also force apex (non-www) -> www to consolidate signals.
https://phonepsychicreaders.com/*  https://www.phonepsychicreaders.com/:splat  301!
http://phonepsychicreaders.com/*   https://www.phonepsychicreaders.com/:splat  301!

